    "created_at": "2014-07-24T14:36:42Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-07-24T14:36:42Z",
    "body": "I think there might still be an issue here. I'm working on an app that needs to be able to do the following:\n1. Load an arbitrary user-supplied web page into a secure container\n2. Inject some Javascript code into the page\n3. Have the page send back a message with results\n\nAt first glance, this would seem be possible in Atom today using a iframe with node-integration=disable and window.postMessage. However, many pages use the X-Frame-Options header to prevent being loaded in an iframe. So that means I have to load these pages in their own window. But with node integration disabled, I don't think there's any way for me to receive messages from that window, or listen for postMessage events.\n\nThoughts? Am I missing something?\n"
  },
