    "updated_at": "2014-07-24T14:57:05Z",
    "body": "@phvcky I think that would work, although I'm not sure if old-fashioned Javascript-based frame-busting would still be an issue. If there's going to be an iframe that acts like a self-contained window, I think the ideal solution would be the ability to embed a BrowserWindow or WebContents in a page, similar to the [webview tag in Chrome apps](https://developer.chrome.com/apps/tags/webview). Of course, that would still leave the problem of not being able to listen for postMessage events on the embedded WebContents.\n"
